      • setMaximumScale

        public void setMaximumScale(long maximumScale)
        Description copied from interface: Layer
        Set the maximum scale. This is the scale that if you zoom in to a more detailed scale than the maximum scale the layer will not be visible. This is inverse from the logical definition of maximum. If scale < maximumScale it will not be shown.
        Specified by:
        setMaximumScale in interface Layer

      • setMinimumScale

        public void setMinimumScale(long minimumScale)
        Description copied from interface: Layer
        Set the minimum scale. This is the scale that if you zoom out to a less detailed scale than the minimum scale the layer will not be visible. This is inverse from the logical definition of minimum. If scale > minimumScale it will not be shown.
        Specified by:
        setMinimumScale in interface Layer
